&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ng-binding&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;90% and 97% were mixed and formed 94%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/17/04/2.png&quot; style=&quot;height:127px; width:175px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, the mixing ratio is 4 : 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The full mixture is of 28 litres&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4; Quantity of 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; solution &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(= \;\frac{4}{7} \times 28\; \)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 16&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The quantity of 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; solution is 16 litres&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the volume of the two containers be V.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;∵ Milk to water ratio in the first container = 3 ∶ 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Volume covered by milk = 3V/4 and Volume covered by water = V/4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the second container, milk to water ratio = 5 ∶ 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Amount of milk = 5V/7 and amount of water = 2V/7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When both the container&amp;rsquo;s content are mixed, amount of milk =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{{3V}}{4} + \frac{{5V}}{7} = \frac{{21V + 20V}}{{28}} = \frac{{41V}}{{28}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And amount of water =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{V}{4} + \frac{{2V}}{7} = \frac{{7V + 8V}}{{28}} = \frac{{15V}}{{28}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
Now, Ratio of milk to water in the new mixture =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{{\frac{{41V}}{{28}}}}{{\frac{{15V}}{{28}}}} = \frac{{41}}{{15}} = 41\;:15\)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ratio of alcohol and water in first mixture = 2 : 7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ratio of alcohol and water in second mixture = 5 : 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Raito of alcohol and water in new mixture = 4 : 5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Mixture and Allegation method&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/10/F2_Ashish.K_29-10-20_savita_D1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 132px; height: 175px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fraction of alcohol in first mixture = 2/(2 + 7) = 2/9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fraction of alcohol in second mixture = 5/(5 + 4) = 5/9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fraction of alcohol in new mixture = 4/(4 + 5) = 4/9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the above formula&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/10/F2_Ashish.K_29-10-20_savita_D3.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 261px; height: 160px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, let the quantity of Zinc to be added be y kg&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The initial total quantity of German Silver is 54 kg&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, we can obtain the initial quantities of the various metals as:&lt;/p&gt;

