&lt;p&gt;After y kg of zinc is added, the ratio of copper, zinc and nickel becomes 2&amp;nbsp;∶ 5&amp;nbsp;∶ 1.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, let the new respective quantities of these metals be 2x, 5x, and x respectively.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, x = 12&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the new quantity of zinc becomes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;18 + y = 5x&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ----(i)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On substituting the value of x = 12 into the equation (i), we get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;y = (5&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 12)&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 18 = 42&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The required quantity of zinc to be added is 42 kg&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

