&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Milk 1: 24% concentration&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Milk 2: 72% concentration&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Quantity of Milk 2 = 18 litres&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mixture required = 36% concentration&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Allegation rule: &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{\text{Quantity of weaker}}{\text{Quantity of stronger}} = \frac{\text{Higher %} - \text{Mean %}}{\text{Mean %} - \text{Lower %}} \)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Ratio = (72 &amp;minus; 36) : (36 &amp;minus; 24) = 36 : 12 = 3 : 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Milk with 72% : Milk with 24% = 1 : 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If 18 litres is from 72%, then 24% part = 18 &amp;times; 3 = 54 litres&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; Required quantity of 24% milk = 54 litres&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
